{{for|the Russian athlete|Aleksandr Markin (athlete)}} {{Infobox football biography | image = | name = Aleksandr Markin | fullname = Aleksandr Andreyevich Markin | birth_date = {{birth date|1949|10|10|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Magnitogorsk]], [[Russian SFSR]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1996|9|2|1949|10|10|df=yes}} | death_place = [[St. Petersburg]], [[Russia]] | height = {{height|m=1.80}} | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | currentclub = | clubnumber = | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[FC Metallurg Magnitogorsk]] | years1 = 1967 | clubs1 = [[FC Metallurg Magnitogorsk]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 1968–1970 | clubs2 = [[FC SKA Khabarovsk]] | caps2 = 83 | goals2 = 16 | years3 = 1971–1974 | clubs3 = [[FC Zvezda Perm]] | caps3 = 111 | goals3 = 51 | years4 = 1975–1977 | clubs4 = [[FC Zenit Leningrad]] | caps4 = 68 | goals4 = 26 | years5 = 1978–1979 | clubs5 = [[FC SKA Rostov-on-Don]] | caps5 = 51 | goals5 = 19 | years6 = 1980 | clubs6 = [[FC Lokomotiv Chelyabinsk]] | caps6 = 33 | goals6 = 10 | pcupdate = | ntupdate = }}
'''Aleksandr Andreyevich Markin''' ({{lang-ru|Александр Андреевич Маркин}}; 10 October 1949 in [[Magnitogorsk]] &ndash; 2 September 1996 in [[St. Petersburg]] in an apartment fire) was a [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[Russia]]n [[association football|football]] player.
He is most notable as the top scorer of the [[1976 Soviet Top League|1976 (autumn) Soviet Top League]] with 13 goals. He was the first [[FC Zenit St. Petersburg]] player to become a top scorer and the only Zenit player to score 4 goals in a league game.
He was also the top scorer in the 1974 season of the [[Soviet First League]] with 25 goals.
