{{Infobox football biography | name = Gerard Aafjes | fullname = Gerard Aafjes | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1985|1|27|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Mijdrecht]], [[Netherlands]] | height = {{height|m=1.81}} | position = [[Defender (football)|Defender]] | currentclub = [[Quick Boys]] | clubnumber = | years1 = 2004–2007 | clubs1 = [[FC Volendam]] | caps1 = 52 | goals1 = 2 | years2 = 2007–2009 | clubs2 = [[Falkirk F.C.|Falkirk]] | caps2 = 43 | goals2 = 1 | years3 = 2009–2011 | clubs3 = [[MVV Maastricht]] | caps3 = 58 | goals3 = 3 | years4 = 2011–2013 | clubs4 = [[PEC Zwolle|FC Zwolle]] | caps4 = 16 | goals4 = 0 | years5 = 2013–2014 | clubs5 = [[Vejle Boldklub|Vejle BK]] | caps5 = 6 | goals5 = 0 | years6 = 2014– | clubs6 = [[Quick Boys]] | caps6 = | goals6 = | club-update = 21:27, 15 December 2010 (UTC) }}
'''Gerard Aafjes''' ({{IPA-nl|ˈɣeːrɑrt ˈaːfjəs}}; born 27 January 1985) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[Football (soccer)|football]] [[Defender (football)|defender]] who plays for [[Quick Boys]] in the 4th tier of Dutch football, the [[Hoofdklasse]].
==Club career== Aafjes was born in [[Mijdrecht]] and joined [[FC Volendam]] in 2004. He later signed a two-year deal with Falkirk in 2007, where he scored once against Inverness Caledonian Thistle.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_prem/7158979.stm |title=Falkirk 1-0 Inverness CT |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=26 December 2007 |accessdate=17 January 2010}}</ref> He joined MVV in the summer of 2009, signing a deal that will keep him with the club until 2011.<ref>[http://www.vi.nl/Nieuws-item/165939/MVV-versterkt-zich-met-Aafjes-Berger-en-Spasojevic.htm "MVV versterkt zich met Aafjes, Berger en Spasojevic"] Voetbal International (1 July 2009)</ref>
On 1 October 2013 Aafjes signed a contract with Danish club [[Vejle Boldklub]]. He came to the club on a free transfer. The contract runs out in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vejle-boldklub.dk/index.php?spiller=7211 |title=Player profile |publisher=[[Vejle Boldklub]] |date=1 October 2013 |accessdate=9 November 2013}}</ref> In summer 2014, Aafjes returned to Holland to play for [[Hoofdklasse|fourth-tier]] [[Quick Boys]].<ref>[http://www.omroepwest.nl/sport/03-08-2014/quick-boys-trekt-voormalig-profvoetballer-gerard-aafjes-aan Quick Boys trekt voormalig profvoetballer Gerard Aafjes aan] - Omroep West {{nl|icon}}</ref>
